<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-0462 </DOCNO><TEXT>To assist the Environmental Protection Agency in evaluating releases froma variety of combinations of geologic settings, radionuclide inventories,mechanisms, and pathways for radioactive releases, time frames, and dose-uptakepathways, a computer model based on the results of these technical investigationswas developed. The model is called REPRISK. The report is documentationfor the REPRISK code. It concentrates on the mechanics of the model.</TEXT></DOC>